---
permalink: /sitemap.xml
---
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<urlset xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:image="http://www.google.com/schemas/sitemap-image/1.1" xmlns="http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9">
    <url>
        <loc>https://www.alphasoftwaregroup.com/</loc>
        <xhtml:link rel="alternate" hreflang="vi" href="https://www.alphasoftwaregroup.com/"/>
        <xhtml:link rel="alternate" hreflang="en" href="https://www.alphasoftwaregroup.com/en/"/>
        <xhtml:link rel="alternate" hreflang="x-default" href="https://www.alphasoftwaregroup.com/"/>
        <lastmod>2026-07-02</lastmod>
    </url>
    <url>
        <loc>https://www.alphasoftwaregroup.com/en/</loc>
        <xhtml:link rel="alternate" hreflang="en" href="https://www.alphasoftwaregroup.com/en/"/>
        <xhtml:link rel="alternate" hreflang="vi" href="https://www.alphasoftwaregroup.com/"/>
        <xhtml:link rel="alternate" hreflang="x-default" href="https://www.alphasoftwaregroup.com/"/>
        <lastmod>2026-07-02</lastmod>
    </url>
    <url>
        <loc>{{ site.url }}/chia-se-kinh-nghiem/</loc>
        <lastmod>{{ site.time | date: "%Y-%m-%d" }}</lastmod>
    </url>
    <url>
        <loc>{{ site.url }}/chia-se-kinh-nghiem/tac-gia/{{ site.data.chia_se_kinh_nghiem.author.slug }}/</loc>
        <lastmod>{{ site.time | date: "%Y-%m-%d" }}</lastmod>
    </url>
{%- comment -%}
  One page per topic, listed straight from the taxonomy — a new topic gets its
  sitemap entry as soon as it has a page and a post.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- for kt_pair in site.data.chia_se_kinh_nghiem.topics %}
{%- assign kt_count = site.posts | where: "topic", kt_pair[0] | size %}
{%- if kt_count > 0 %}
    <url>
        <loc>{{ site.url }}/chia-se-kinh-nghiem/chu-de/{{ kt_pair[0] }}/</loc>
        <lastmod>{{ site.time | date: "%Y-%m-%d" }}</lastmod>
    </url>
{%- endif %}
{%- endfor %}
{%- comment -%}
  Chia sẻ kinh nghiệm articles are generated from _posts automatically — a new post needs
  no sitemap edit. The emitted <lastmod> is a build-date placeholder; the
  update-sitemap.mjs step rewrites it honestly (keeps the previous date unless
  the page's built HTML actually changed).

  Each article also declares its picture through the image sitemap extension, so
  the infographics can be found in Google Images on their own — a second doorway
  into the article. Google reads only <image:loc> today (the caption/title tags
  were retired), so the alt text in the markup is what describes them.
{%- endcomment %}
{%- for post in site.posts %}
    <url>
        <loc>{{ site.url }}{{ post.url }}</loc>
        <lastmod>{{ site.time | date: "%Y-%m-%d" }}</lastmod>
{%- if post.image %}
{%- assign kt_img = site.data.chia_se_kinh_nghiem.images[post.image] %}
        <image:image>
            <image:loc>{{ site.url }}/img/chia-se-kinh-nghiem/{{ post.image }}-{{ kt_img.w }}.jpg</image:loc>
        </image:image>
{%- endif %}
    </url>
{%- endfor %}
</urlset>
